# 🧠 Customer Churn Prediction with Machine Learning

A complete machine learning pipeline to predict customer churn, extract business insights, and deploy an interactive web dashboard using Streamlit.

---

## 🔍 Problem Statement

Customer churn is a key metric for business sustainability. This project predicts whether a customer is likely to churn using historical data from a telecom company. Early detection allows businesses to take corrective action and reduce churn rates.

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies

- Python
- Pandas, NumPy, Seaborn, Matplotlib
- Scikit-learn (Logistic Regression, Random Forest)
- Streamlit (App Deployment)
- Jupyter Notebook
- GitHub

---

## 📊 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

- Overall churn rate: **26.5%**
- Monthly contract customers churn more than long-term
- Churn highly correlated with:
  - Contract Type
  - Customer Service Calls
  - Electronic Billing
  - Tenure & Internet Service Type

![EDA Visual](images/eda_visual.png)

---

## 🔧 Feature Engineering

- Label encoded categorical features
- Binned tenure into categories (e.g., short, medium, long)
- Engineered total services used
- Handled missing values

---

## 🤖 Model Building & Evaluation

| Model               | Accuracy | ROC AUC |
|--------------------|----------|---------|
| Logistic Regression| 79.8%    | 0.84    |
| Random Forest      | 81.6%    | 0.85    |

✅ Final model: **Random Forest**  
✅ Balanced performance + feature interpretability

